"<p>&nbsp;What would you consider today&rsquo;s most coveted status symbols? A Mercedes or a Ferrari, a diamond Rolex or a designer handbag? A European villa? In Rachel Ruysch&rsquo;s day it was a simple tulip. Looking at her floral still life paintings can reveal an entire hidden world&mdash;of wealth, status, even the economics of the world&rsquo;s first financial crises.&nbsp;</p>\n"
