"\n"
"<p>Both buildings pre-date the Pavilion. Moreover, juxtaposing a culturally alien interior to the exterior was not a new idea, and was in some sense&nbsp;a colonial interpretation of the cultures of the lands of Empire. Henry Holland&#39;s French Neo-classical Carlton House,&nbsp;1783&ndash;96&nbsp;in London, for example, boasted a fine Chinese drawing room. As such, Brighton Pavilion could be seen as the culmination of years of experimentation, rather than a one-off, stand-alone enterprise.<br />\n"
"<br />\n"
