"<h3>Botticelli&rsquo;s drawings</h3>\n"
"\n"
"<p>In his <em>Lives of the Artists</em>, Giorgio Vasari wrote; &quot;since Sandro was also a learned man, he wrote a commentary on part of Dante&rsquo;s poem, and after illustrating the<em> Inferno</em>, he printed the work.&quot;&nbsp;Either Vasari was a bit misinformed, or he was implying something regarding the profound interrelations between the texts and images when he said that Sandro Botticelli &quot;wrote a commentary.&quot;&nbsp; In fact, in the 1480s&mdash;the same decade when he painted his most infamous works, <em>Primavera</em> and <em>The Birth of Venus</em>&mdash;Botticelli undertook the task of drawing not only the <em>Inferno</em> but the entire <em>Divine Comedy</em>. &nbsp;</p>\n"
"\n"
