"<h3><span>The First Emperor</span></h3>\n"
"\n"
"<p>Qin Shihuang (259-210 B.C.E.) conquered much in this life, but his driving purpose was even greater;&nbsp;he sought to conquer death.&nbsp;In order to achieve immortality, he built himself a tomb&mdash;a vast underground city guarded by a life-size terracotta army including warriors, infantrymen, horses, chariots and all their attendant armor and weaponry.</p>\n"
"\n"
