"<p>While one may be inclined to emphasize how &ldquo;foreign&rdquo; the medieval book is&mdash;they are, after all, made of dead cows, and are handwritten&mdash;they present such recognizably modern features as a justified text, footnotes, running titles and page numbers.</p>\n"
"\n"
